            "answer_text": "Let angle A = x Angle B = y As mentioned in the question angle C = 3 angle B = 3y Angle C is also given as 2(Angle A + Angle B) = 2(x+y) So, 3y = 2(x+y) y = 2x So angle C = 3y = 6x We know that sum of all the 3 angles in a triangle = 180deg Therefore, Angle A+ Angle B + Angle C = 180 x+ 2x+ 6x = 180 x = 20 Hence Angle A = 20 Angle B = 40 Angle C = 120 ",
